==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Witless
<hw>Wit"less</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Destitute of wit or
understanding; wanting thought; hence, indiscreet; not under the
guidance of judgment.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Witless</xex> bravery.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A witty mother! <qex>witless</qex> else her son.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Witless</qex> pity breedeth fruitless love.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Wit"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Wit"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Witling</ent>⟦br⟧
